<div id="banner">
	<h1>What can you say to that?</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>In olden days, children used to whine to their parents and parents would reply by telling them how they have it so much better than those kids in China.</p>

<p>In modern days, children whine on their blog and the kids in China tell them themselves.</p>

<p>I wrote:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Today was packed with work non-stop from 7am until 7pm. When it was over I was so filled with anxiety over uncompleted tasks that I could hardly sit or walk. </p>
</blockquote>

<p>So &#8220;kk&#8221; <a href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/001576#c4022">commented</a>:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Are u always so busy?</p>
  
  <p>so you have many tasks to finish everyday?think about we chinese students,we are doing exercises everyday!</p>
</blockquote>

<p>And his IP address shows that yes, he really is from China. Wow. What can you say to that?</p>

<p class="posted">posted February 27, 2005 02:31 PM (<a class="category" href="cat_education">Education</a>) (<a href="#comments">7 comments</a>) <a href="001598" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

